## Backend behavior note (surface, do not paper over)

`GET /api/quotation/quotes/{id}` returns only the rolled-up `headcount`, not `aggregateCensus.planBreakdown`. The PUT accepts and persists the breakdown server-side, but the GET-response shape omits it. Consequence: after Save + page reload, the editable table seeds each row to 0 again (the user can no longer see the per-plan allocation they just submitted).

This is a backend response-shape gap, not a frontend bug. Two paths forward:
- (Backend) Add `aggregateCensus` to the QuoteDto response shape — DSL already has `aggregateCensus: AggregateCensus?` on the Quote entity (`docs/spec/quotation/QuotationDomain.domain:25`), so the response is silently missing a documented field.
- (Frontend interim) None warranted — per CORE_MEMORY honesty pattern, do not mock-fix what backend should expose.

Filed as a follow-up note in PROP-0005's Implementation notes; surfaced here so a backend ticket can be filed against group-pas. No build action.

